               <p>Tried by the second Middlesex Jury before Mr. 
               <persName id="t17831029-18-person327">
                  Baron
                   EYRE
               <interp inst="t17831029-18-person327" type="surname" value="EYRE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17831029-18-person327" type="given" value="Baron"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17831029-18-person327" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. I beg your Lordship to shew mercy to Shipley, I have reason to think he was drawn in by this old offender Templar.</p>
               <p>Court. Have you any reason to think Templar an old offender? - Yes, I do, and I think Shipley never was guilty of any thing of the kind before.</p>
